Senior/Engineering Assistant (RMT/201404/04/SG)
Job ID
EPM-00007557
Country
Singapore
State/Province
Singapore
City
Singapore
Publish Start Date
Apr 23 2014
Job Level
Experienced (Non-Manager)
|
Responsibilities:
Responsible for maintaining the uptime of production line equipments and facilities, hence the reduction in redlight response time.
Design and/or modify current equipments to improve OEE (Overall Equipment Effectiveness) and/or improve line productivity.
Work with engineers to setup new product lines or bring in new capabilities/capacity.
Perform Preventive Maintenance on equipments and take corrective actions on abnormalities found.
Work with production to ensure that all calibrated equipments are within calibration schedule and equipments meet government (NEA/MOM) regulations during inspections.
Requirements:
Diploma in Mechanical, Electrical, Electronic, Mechatronic Engineering preferably with more than 1 year experience.
Able to work independently, initiative and teamwork.
Knowledge of PLC (Programmable Logic Controller) preferred.